wdi2-SH.ANM.ALLW.ZS.def: Prevalence of anemia among women of reproductive age refers to the combined prevalence of both non-pregnant with haemoglobin levels below 12 g/dL and pregnant women with haemoglobin levels below 11 g/dL.
wdi2-SH.ANM.ALLW.ZS.name: Prevalence of anemia among women of reproductive age
wdi2-SH.ANM.ALLW.ZS.source: World Health Organization, Global Health Observatory Data Repository/World Health Statistics.
